            "id": "4432008",
            "title": "Nasdaq, S&P, Dow futures rise after tech led selloff",
            "description": "<html><body><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Stock index futures were higher on Thursday, while yields gained, as Wall Street hoped for a rebound a day after a tech-driven selloff.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">S&amp;P 500 futures (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPX\" title=\"S&amp;P 500 Index\">SPX</a></span></span>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+0.8%</span>, Nasdaq 100 futures (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US100:IND\" title=\"NASDAQ 100 Futures\">US100:IND</a>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+1%</span>, and Dow futures (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INDU\" title=\"Dow Jones Futures\">INDU</a></span></span>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+0.9%</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The 10-year Treasury yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US10Y\" title=\"United States 10-Year Bond Yield\">US10Y</a>) rose 3 basis points to 4.32%. The 2-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US2Y\" title=\"United States 2-Year Bond Yield\">US2Y</a>) rose 3 basis points to 3.82%.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Wall Street on Wednesday ended deep in the red after Federal Reserve Chair <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4431746-tariffs-could-create-tension-between-feds-dual-mandate-goals-fed-chair-jerome-powell-says\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Jerome Powell\">Jerome Powell</a> expressed concerns about the likely higher-than-anticipated effects from tariffs, including possibly putting pressure on the central bank's dual mandate of stable prices and strong employment.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"Ahead of the Easter weekend, risk assets sold off again, as ongoing trade tensions and hawkish comments from Fed Chair Powell led to growing concern about the near-term outlook, particularly if the Fed would be reluctant to ease policy,\" Deutsche Bank's Henry Allen said.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"In terms of the latest on the trade front, investors were most concerned about chipmakers yesterday, which followed the new restrictions from the Donald Trump administration on semiconductor exports to China,\" Allen said.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">On the economic front, eyes will be on the March housing starts and permits, initial jobless claims, and the April Philly Fed business outlook, all landing at the same time.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The initial jobless claims are expected to rise to 225K, and the Philly Fed business outlook is anticipated to come in at  2.2.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\"The US Philly Fed business sentiment survey is due. All sentiment data is extremely suspect nowadays, but markets are focused on the corporate inactivity amidst policy uncertainty. Even unreliable evidence, therefore, has influence,\" UBS' Paul Donovan said.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Markets will be closed tomorrow on account of Good Friday.</p>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/165090199/image_165090199.jpg?io=getty-c-w750",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4432008-sp500-nasdaq-dow-jones-outlook-stock-market",
            "pub_date": "2025-04-17 17:46:49",
