            "id": "4432012",
            "title": "Goldman Sachs warns of potential $800B U.S. selloff in Chinese stocks",
            "description": "<html><body><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Goldman Sachs has issued a stark warning about the financial risks posed by growing tensions between the U.S. and China. In an extreme scenario of financial decoupling, U.S. investors could be forced to divest as much as $800 billion worth of Chinese equities, the investment bank estimates.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Currently, about 7% of the market capitalization of Chinese firms' American Depositary Receipts (ADRs) is held by U.S. institutions. These investors may face limitations in trading Hong Kong-listed shares, particularly if major companies like Alibaba face involuntary delisting from U.S. exchanges, Goldman analysts noted.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The bank's analysis adds to mounting concerns from global financial institutions as the possibility of a U.S.-China financial split becomes more tangible amid escalating trade and regulatory friction.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>China ETFs:</strong> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KWEB\" title=\"KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF\">KWEB</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PGJ\" title=\"Invesco Golden Dragon China ETF\">PGJ</a></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FXI\" title=\"iShares China Large-Cap ETF\">FXI</a></span>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ASHR\" title=\"Deutsche X-trackers Harvest CSI 300 China A-Shares ETF\">ASHR</a>), (YIN), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/YANG\" title=\"Direxion Daily FTSE China Bear 3x Shares ETF\">YANG</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GXC\" title=\"SPDR S&amp;P China ETF\">GXC</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FXP\" title=\"ProShares UltraShort FTSE China 25 ETF\">FXP</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KBA\" title=\"KraneShares Bosera MSCI China A ETF\">KBA</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CXSE\" title=\"WisdomTree China ex-State-Owned Enterprises ETF\">CXSE</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CNYA\" title=\"iShares MSCI China A ETF\">CNYA</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CHAU\" title=\"Direxion Daily CSI 300 China A Share Bull 2x Shares ETF\">CHAU</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FLCH\" title=\"Franklin FTSE China ETF\">FLCH</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/YXI\" title=\"ProShares Trust - ProShares Short FTSE China 50\">YXI</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FCA\" title=\"First Trust Exchange-Traded AlphaDEX Fund II - First Trust China AlphaDEX Fund\">FCA</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KALL\" title=\"KraneShares Trust - KraneShares MSCI All China Index ETF\">KALL</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/JCHI\" title=\"JPMorgan Active China ETF\">JCHI</a>)</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The trade war between the world’s two largest economies continues to weigh on global markets and economic growth. Earlier this month, Trump escalated a tense trade war with China by raising tariffs to a cumulative 145%, prompting a swift retaliation from Beijing with a 125% duty on U.S. goods.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The offshore yuan (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CNY:USD\" title=\"Chinese Yuan / US Dollar\">CNY:USD</a>) fell nearly<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> 0.2% </span>against the dollar at the time of writing. The Australian dollar (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AUD:USD\" title=\"Australian Dollar / US Dollar\">AUD:USD</a>), a China-proxy currency, was also down <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">0.24%</span>. S&amp;P 500 (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPX\" title=\"S&amp;P 500 Index\">SPX</a></span></span></span></span>) Index futures were up<span style=\"color: #008000;\"> 0.83%</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>US-listed Chinese stocks of relevance:</strong> Alibaba (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BABA\" title=\"Alibaba Group Holding Limited\">BABA</a>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+4.4% premarket</span>, Baidu (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BIDU\" title=\"Baidu, Inc.\">BIDU</a>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+2.69%</span>, PDD (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PDD\" title=\"PDD Holdings Inc.\">PDD</a>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+1.79%</span>, JD.com (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/JD\" title=\"JD.com, Inc.\">JD</a>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+1.61%</span>, NetEase (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NTES\" title=\"NetEase, Inc.\">NTES</a>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+4.2%</span>, Trip.com (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TCOM\" title=\"Trip.com Group Limited\">TCOM</a>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+3.76%</span>.</p>\n</body></html>",
